e319e9937e9280e47fdf26be80099434.name: Cho Dang Gol
e319e9937e9280e47fdf26be80099434.about: Cho Dang Gol is a Korean restaurant located in the heart of New York City that offers something different than the plethora of Asian restaurants populating the city. We specialize in home-made tofu, made in the traditional style of Chodanggol, a small coastal village in Korea. We strive to preserve the authentic taste of regional Korean cuisine while incorporating our fresh tofu. We look forward to serving you!

history.description: CDG is known as "Tofu House" for its various homemade tofu based menus, which they make freshly every morning. Some of the popular menus include Dumpling Jeongol (spicy hot pot with kimchi, homemade dumplings and tofu, squid, pork and assorted vegetables), Dubu Duruchigi (spicy stir-fried pork with homemade tofu), and Soybean Paste Stew (traditional stew with assorted vegetables). Jeon or Korean style pancakes are also popular with variety of topping such as seafood, kabocha, teri- yaki chicken, cod fish, assorted mushroom, and more). CDG not only offers traditional Korean dishes, but also offers new recipes through weekly and seasonal specials, for those who are looking for even more variety within Korean cuisine.

441b5d5c48a5ffcdded11e1b9d396030.name: Thursday Kitchen
441b5d5c48a5ffcdded11e1b9d396030.about: "Thursday, the ambiguous weekend." We here at the Thursday Kitchen want to clear up that ambiguity by providing lively music, amazing food, fun drinks and good vibes. We have created a restaurant where you can celebrate weekend feels everyday of the week. Every Thursday, here at Thursday, our staff dedicates one more hour of service and play more lively music to celebrate the start of the weekend. Only cool people invited. Owner/Chef kay believes cooking is one of the arts that does not have limit. She also uses cooking to communicate with others. As you taste and try her New Korean language please feel free to reply back to her with opinions and favorites. It is really hard to define what kind of cuisine thursday kitchen is because our culture is limitless and we decided to call it new korean. We put great detail and care with every meal and moment also our team serves you with passion and soul. Please check our team, who enjoy making people happy.

history.description: Owner Chef Kyungmin Kay Hyun’s love for a wide spread of cultures and cuisine makes it hard to place her cooking in a specific category. That is why her own concept of “New Korean” was born. With Chef Kay South Korean background, French cuisine training, and an exceptional love for spanish food, Thursday Kitchen offers a unique blend of international elements in ingredients and flavor in a tapas style fashion. You may be wondering, “Why Thursday?” Typically, the weekend seems to start on fridays, making Thursday night plans uncertain. At Thursday Kitchen, we want to turn that uncertain feeling into a kind of excitement that only we can offer with our quality of food, service, and overall good vibes

0193e9bf41e76b9cd576278ee48ff9e5.name: ZEYTUN NYC
0193e9bf41e76b9cd576278ee48ff9e5.about: Each dish tells a tale of its own from ancient times. Rich in taste and aroma, served with a smile, each dish is a must-try. We will get you hooked to our taste. We specialize in Traditional Pakistani, Premium Quality Cuisines. Our taste is best in town and we have the most raving fans. ZEYTUN NYC exists to cherish Special taste that makes our clients bond with Pakistani food & culture even stronger.

history.description: Pakistanis love food. We eat a lot of good food in any one day and we share our special dishes with our friends, neighbors, and colleagues, which makes us feel good. That's who we are :) And That's how this catering business started. After years of sharing my super delicious food with everyone around me and them telling me that I should start charging for my recipes and skills, I finally decided to open up a catering company. And from the beginning, I made sure that our business gives back in multiple meaningful ways so we started a free training program for the women survivors of human trafficking who are living in safe-houses and regular shelters in NYC. Our business model serves as a training academy and every 6 months a batch of 10 women survivors will be passing out equipped with the skills to start their lives from the ground up, free, strong, and financially independent. If you want to become part of our mission, please feel free to reach out to us.
